      "message": "Here too.\n\nIf you implemented the checking, I think everything would all work out more compactly too, because you’d be able to share the EXPECT_EQ that you care about.\n\nLike, above\n\n#if defined(OS_ANDROID)\n  const int android_runtime_api \u003d FigureItOut();\n#else\n  // glibc’s loader implements all of the tested features that Android’s was \n  // once missing but has since gained.\n  const int android_runtime_api \u003d std::numeric_limits\u003cint\u003e::max();\n#endif\n\nthen here, the much more compact\n\n  if (android_runtime_api \u003e\u003d 23) {\n    EXPECT_EQ(module.load_bias, module_reader.GetLoadBias());\n  }",
